Test-Specific

Test::Specific offers Test::More style test functions that are more specific than "ok()".

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Build.PL
    ./Build
    ./Build test
    ./Build install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    perldoc Test::Specific

You can also look for information at:

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Test-Specific

    CPAN Request Tracker:
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Test-Specific

    AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Test-Specific

    CPAN Ratings:
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Test-Specific

